defs.def: (baseball) an advance to first base by a batter who receives four balls
the act of traveling by foot

examples.example: he took a walk after lunch

defs.def: a slow gait of a horse in which two feet are always on the ground

examples.example: it happens in all walks of life

defs.def: a path set aside for walking

examples.example: after the blizzard he shoveled the front walk

defs.def: give a base on balls to
take a walk; go for a walk; walk for pleasure

examples.example: The lovers held hands while walking
We like to walk every Sunday

defs.def: use one's feet to advance; advance by steps

examples.example: She walks with a slight limp
He walks the horse up the mountain
I'll walk you to your car
Paul walked the streets of Damascus
The horses walked across the meadow

defs.def: be or act in association with

examples.example: We must walk with our dispossessed brothers and sisters

defs.def: live or behave in a specified manner

g.def: to travel a distance by walking
maintained place on which to walk
het lopend afleggen van een bepaalde afstand
Se [[déplacer]] par un mouvement alternatif des [[jambe]]s ou des [[patte]]s, en ayant toujours un appui au sol.
Mener, conduire, faire aller quelqu’un de côté ou d’autre.
